Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
ecoMergeCombinationalCell(25.10)              ecoMergeCombinationalCell(25.10)

Name
       ecoMergeCombinationalCell  -  Merges combinational cells into multi-bit
       cells for the specified instance

Syntax
       ecoMergeCombinationalCell

       [-help]

       [-area]

       [-cell <target_cell_name_list>]

       [-force]

       -inst <comboInstName> | -listFile <instNamesFile> | -all

       [-power]

       -preCTS | -postCTS

       Merges combinational cells into multi-bit cells for the  specified  in-
       stance.  You can specify the names of the combinational instances to be
       merged or you can specify the file containing names of single  bit  in-
       stances to merge.

       Naming Convention During Merging

       When the combinational cells in the specified file are merged, the cor-
       responding instance names are combined as follows:

              * hier1/hier2/i_0   +   hier1/hier2/i_1   +   hier1/hier2/i_2  +
                hier1/hier2/i_3

                TO

                hier1/hier2/CDN_MB_i_0_MB_i_1_MB_i_2_MB_i_3

              * abc_x[0] + abc_x[1] + abc_x[2] + abc_x[3]

                TO

                CDN_MB_abc_x[0]_MB_x[1]_MB_x[2]_MB_x[3]

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for  each  ecoMergeCombinationalCell parameter. For a
              detailed description of the command and all of  its  parameters,
              use the man command:  man ecoMergeCombinationalCell.

       -all   Specifies  that  all  single-bit cell instances should be merged
              into multi-bit cell instances.

              This parameter is mutually exclusive with the -listFile and -all
              parameters. At least one of these parameters must be specified.

       -area  Specifies to merge the combinational cells for area purposes.

              Default: false

       -cell<target_cell_name_list>
              Specifies the list of all multibit combinational cells as target
              cells to merge. This parameter is only relevant  in  the  preCTS
              flow.

              Example,

              ecoMergeCombinationalCell -all -preCTS -cell {<<list>>}

              Default: ""

       -force Forces  the  merging of the combinational cell regardless of the
              timing gains.

              Default: false

       -inst <comboInstName>
              Specifies the name of the combinational instance to  be  merged.
              This is a required parameter.

              This parameter is mutually exclusive with the -listFile and -all
              parameters. At least one of these parameters must be specified.

       -postCTS
              Specify this parameter if the design stage is postCTS.

              Note:  This parameter is mutually exclusive with the -preCTS pa-
              rameter. One of the two parameters must be specified.

       -listFile <instNamesFile>
              Specifies the file containing the names of single bit  instances
              to  merge.  Specify  one  instance on one line. Comment with in-
              stance name should not contain spaces or backslashes

              This parameter is mutually exclusive with the -inst and -all pa-
              rameters. At least one of these parameters must be specified.

       -power Specify this parameter to  merge  the  combinational  cells  for
              power purposes.

              Default: false

       -preCTS
              Specify this parameter if the design stage is preCTS.

              Note: This parameter is mutually exclusive with the -postCTS pa-
              rameter. One of the two parameters must be specified.

